Randolph had a recurring role as Louise the Maid on CBS's The Danny Thomas Show and appeared in the show's 1967 reunion program, which aired shortly after her death.
In 1955, Amanda opened a restaurant in Los Angeles called "Mama's Place", where she did the cooking.

Despite all her film and television work, Randolph found herself slightly short of the requirements for a much-needed Screen Actors Guild pension at the age of 70 (both sisters had struggled for roles in the late 1930s).
She married Harry Hansberry sometime after 1940.
They were estranged when Hansberry died of a heart attack in 1961.
Randolph died of a stroke in Duarte, California, on August 24, 1967, aged 70.
